AS (Alias)
5. Write a query to show customer name as Buyer and price as Unit_Price.
mysql> select customer_name as buyer,price as unit_price from orders;
+---------+------------+
| buyer   | unit_price |
+---------+------------+
| Alice   |    1200.00 |
| Bob     |     650.50 |
| Charlie |     300.00 |
| Diana   |     199.99 |
| Ethan   |      49.99 |
| Fiona   |      25.00 |
+---------+------------+
6. Write a query to show order ID and total amount (quantity Ã— price) as Total_Cost.
mysql> select order_id,(quantity*price) as total_cost from orders;
+----------+------------+
| order_id | total_cost |
+----------+------------+
|        1 |    1200.00 |
|        2 |    1301.00 |
|        3 |     300.00 |
|        4 |     599.97 |
|        5 |     249.95 |
|        6 |     100.00 |
+----------+------------+
NOT
7. Write a query to find all orders not placed by Bob.
mysql> select * from orders where customer_name!='bob';
